        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "We proceed now to the proof. Assume by way of contradiction that there exist a, b € G with a x b # 0. Put c = ax b = a*b, so that a,b, e are nonzero and linSay independents Vete be the id in element bad. exa=exb= exc=0. Since a, b, e span R3, ex* =0 for all * E R', so e = 0.",
